See http://projects.ez.no/ezvideoflv

Provides a new datatype that handles video files and converts them into FLV so
that they can be read with a web FLV player (like on Youtube or Dailymotion).
It is based on the ezmedia datatype. It also produces an image preview for  each videos.

Features :
	* Store video files
	* Convert to FLV on upload or with a cronjob script
	* Produce a preview for each videos

Requirements :
    * eZ Publish 3.9 or better
	* ffmpeg-php module
	* a video converter like ffmpeg (default configuration)
	* flash player to see videos

Install :
0. Install requirements (ffmpeg-php and ffmpeg binary)
1. Download the archive
2. Unpack it in the extension directory of eZ Publish
3. Execute ezvideoflv.sql script, for exemple from the eZ Publish root :
	* mysql -u login -p base < extension/ezvideoflv/sql/ezvideoflv.sql
4. Activate the extension width the Administration interface in System >
   Extensions
5. Configure cronjob, for example run the following command line every 5 minutes
   	* php4 runcronjobs.php flv
6. Add video/read function to role policies of users that should be able to read
   videos.

Configuration :
Comments in settings/ezvideoflv.ini.append.php gives information on how to
configure the extension.
Default configuration :
	* it uses ffmpeg to convert video files
	* it uses cronjobs script for files over 2Mo
	* it produces preview in JPEG in var/your_site/storage/flv_preview use the
	  middle video frame.
	* it uses FLV Player to show videos
To convert videos again with new settings, just run :
 * php4 runcronjobs.php flv -all
